plane-crazy 2020-11-07 08:17:42 Thereby creating a Vip1 meaning that for any Vip to exist > 1 then there needs to be a Vip1
plane-crazy 2020-11-07 08:19:37 My favorite thing to do with arguments is link both sides together
plane-crazy 2020-11-07 08:20:03 Usually leads to "If your side of the argument is true then it is false and mine is true"
plane-crazy 2020-11-07 08:20:38 I will now introduce the mechanics of good game design
plane-crazy 2020-11-07 08:21:22 In a game where you are not spoon fed information by the second it is required to build this information into the environment.
plane-crazy 2020-11-07 08:21:43 Lacking this structure will leave players confused
plane-crazy 2020-11-07 08:22:51 In the instance that a value greater than 1 is attached to the end of an item's name it is typically considered to be a marker that the item is part of a list usually starting with 1
plane-crazy 2020-11-07 08:23:28 with this assumption the player psychologically constructs a 'phantom' vip 1
plane-crazy 2020-11-07 08:24:18 For Vip2 to exist while Vip1 does not exist results in the player assuming there is a Vip1 and constructing an image of it.
plane-crazy 2020-11-07 08:25:11 And now we hit recursion, to simply increment to Vip3 chains down to Vip2 which chains down to Vip1
plane-crazy 2020-11-07 08:25:49 The existence of Vip0 would confuse players and likely result in a link to Vip1 and such for negatives
plane-crazy 2020-11-07 08:27:02 This concludes my deconstruction of an argument to the atomic level and reassembling into a recursive chain to test the strategy, continue doing plane stuff

bug-reports 2020-12-24 02:12:09 Copy and paste does not properly copy recently changed settings
Steps to reproduce error
1: Place 2 Signs or text blocks (Recommend of same type to minimize variables)
2: Change text of first sign (Recommend "Old text A") and close the settings menu
3: Change text of second sign (Recommend "Old text B") and close the settings menu
4: Change text of first sign (Recommend "New text A") and **do not** close the settings menu
5: Press C (**Not** Ctrl+C, though it has similar effect it will break your ability to copy paste anything inside or outside roblox until you leave the game) (Without exiting the settings menu) to copy settings
6: Close settings menu and configure the second sign
7: Press V (**Not** Ctrl+V, effects untested, likely to break copy paste on your device similar to above note on Ctrl+C) to paste settings
8: Sign B should now read the text created before sign A was edited the second time (Recommended should result in "Old text A")

the-dump 2021-02-08 15:41:35 Birdwatching, or birding, is a form of wildlife observation in which the observation of birds is a recreational activity or citizen science. It can be done with the naked eye, through a visual enhancement device like binoculars and telescopes, by listening for bird sounds, or by watching public webcams.

Birdwatching often involves a significant auditory component, as many bird species are more easily detected and identified by ear than by eye. Most birdwatchers pursue this activity for recreational or social reasons, unlike ornithologists, who engage in the study of birds using formal scientific methods.
the-dump 2021-02-08 15:43:06 The early interest in observing birds for their aesthetic rather than utilitarian (mainly food) value is traced to the late 18th century in the works of Gilbert White, Thomas Bewick, George Montagu and John Clare. The study of birds and natural history in general became increasingly prevalent in Britain during the Victorian Era, often associated with collection, eggs and later skins being the artifacts of interest. Wealthy collectors made use of their contacts in the colonies to obtain specimens from around the world. It was only in the late 19th century that the call for bird protection began leading to the rising popularity of observations on living birds. The Audubon Society was started to protect brids from the growing trade in feathers in the United States while the Royal Society for the Protection of Birds began in Britain.

the-dump 2021-02-16 04:01:59 
the-dump 2021-02-16 04:09:30 
the-dump 2021-02-16 04:09:57 
the-dump 2021-02-16 05:28:24 
the-dump 2021-02-16 05:33:56 Subtraction is only to be performed for rank evaluation
the-dump 2021-02-16 05:34:04 upvotes count how many people like your stuff
the-dump 2021-02-16 05:34:21 you don't lose people liking stuff if someone dislikes it
the-dump 2021-02-16 05:36:23 In terms of the average degree of movement it does work
the-dump 2021-02-16 05:36:39 in terms of how many people like it enough to upvote you use upvotes
the-dump 2021-02-16 05:37:23 average degree of movements is by how much does it inspire people to hit one arrow over the other, if you have a very mild creation you will get fewer upvotes but also fewer downvotes
the-dump 2021-02-16 05:38:08 I say instead of raising thresholds, make it ratio based
the-dump 2021-02-16 05:39:36 If 25 people upvote, that's 25 people saying "This person deserves a reward for what they've created"
the-dump 2021-02-16 05:40:27 If 25 downvote that's 25 people saying "This contraption is below average in quality"

the-dump 2021-08-17 00:47:42 - If someone pots out, the time limit no longer matters. The game continues until all winks of a partnership are in the pot. All squops must be squidged. Covering winks are moved to 2mm away from all other winks. Play continues in the regular order. First color to pot out wins.
the-dump 2021-08-17 00:48:01 - To play a squopped wink, you first play the upper surface of the unsquopped wink. Winks vertically below the wink you first touch can be hit by the squidger. The shot has to be short and continuous from start to finish. You could play a pile shot in which you send the enemy wink far away. This is called a boondock.

bot-central 2021-12-25 09:13:31 Tip for minesweeper, if there is an arrangement such as:
bot-central 2021-12-25 09:14:43 Because 7 of 8 areas are confirmed to be safe, the top left square must be a mine according to the 1 in the center of the image
bot-central 2021-12-25 09:18:06 The more safe tiles unlocked around a tile, the more you know about the unknown center
bot-central 2021-12-25 09:20:30 Ahem
bot-central 2021-12-25 09:21:19 As you can see, the goal here is to learn more about the 7 covered tiles before making a guess
bot-central 2021-12-25 09:22:10 If complete tiles were ordered with 1 being top left and 15 being bottom right
bot-central 2021-12-25 09:22:30 Then tile 5 can be determined to be a mine because of the cornered 1 in tile 3
bot-central 2021-12-25 09:23:23 Because tile 5 is a mine and tile 9 is a 2, the only place for the other mine to be is tile 11
bot-central 2021-12-25 09:23:56 so now, the task is to identify the remaining 2 mines in the 3 tiles available
bot-central 2021-12-25 09:24:03 that is how minesweeper works

plane-crazy 2022-02-05 08:28:43 Assuming the 'forward' pitches in a way that points the seat downwards
plane-crazy 2022-02-05 08:29:02 And that the 'upward' causes the blades to angle
plane-crazy 2022-02-05 08:30:11 during upward motion, the blades do provide resistance in the direction of rotation, if there were one blade then the helicopter would wobble from this force and the imbalanced rotor
plane-crazy 2022-02-05 08:30:31 this force is countered by there being multiple blades
plane-crazy 2022-02-05 08:30:40 there is a second resistive force being gravity
plane-crazy 2022-02-05 08:31:34 as you tilt the helicopter with the forward input, while the blades are angled, the force of gravity is uneven on the rotor
plane-crazy 2022-02-05 08:32:02 causing that first upward resistance to try to spin the helicopter
plane-crazy 2022-02-05 08:33:38 this is not the first thing to check for however
plane-crazy 2022-02-05 08:33:43 the things to check for are
plane-crazy 2022-02-05 08:34:14 1: is the helicopter's center of mass to the right or left of the center of symmetry
plane-crazy 2022-02-05 08:34:59 2: is any 'lift' device to the left or right and not matched on the other side
